Mmmm <i>without drastic syntax changes</i>?<p>Classes:<p><pre><code>    There is no semicolon after the function name
    The function keyword is omitted
    There are no commas after each definition
</code></pre>
Interpolation:<p><pre><code>    `${1 + 1}` <- why not just # like everyone else?
</code></pre>
Multi line strings:<p><pre><code>     ` Now we have a 3rd
       string delimiter`
</code></pre>
Fat arrow:<p><pre><code>    $(&quot;button&quot;).on(&quot;click&quot;, () => { 
      // really? hanging parens? no function keyword?
    });
</code></pre>
Destructuring:<p><pre><code>    var [first, , last] = [1, 2, 3]
    // thats a var to assign vals inside an array
    // and just two commas touching to ignore a value

</code></pre>
The whole post is about drastic syntax changes. The brackets are optional in coffeescript.<p>Besides coffeescript is just a tool.
